@endnode

@node help "How to set up the Shell-Startup script"

Below is the listing of the original "S:Shell-Startup" script:

Prompt "%N.%S> "
Alias Clear "Echo *"*E[0;0H*E[J*" "
Alias XCopy "Copy CLONE "


My personal Shell-Startup script looks now like this:

Prompt "*E[0m*E[>2m*E[42m*E[1mErr(%r) Proc(%n) Dir(%s)*E[22m> "
Alias Clear "Echo *"*E[0;0H*E[J*" "
Alias XCopy "Copy CLONE "
Alias View Run >NIL: <NIL: Viewer
Path Work:Tools S: SYS:Rexxc SYS:Utilities SYS:System ADD
CD RAM:
TSM		; Make every Shell an app-window, path for TSM is "C:"

@endnode
